history.content:
https://eecs.berkeley.edu/resources/undergrads/eecs/degree-reqs/enrollment-policy

According to that, "A small number of seats will be held for declared CS juniors and seniors and non-EECS, College of Engineering majors," so if you phase I, you could enroll directly if you have an early phase I time.

children.subject: From experience, I recommend phase 1 because the class tends to not expand like the lower div CS ones do. If you don't have an early appointment, phase 1 + sad 8AM lab time should give you a high chance of being enrolled.

Do phase 1 to get the best lab time. Because for ee16b you need to use the oscilloscope and power supply the class cannot be expanded and because labs are very long, you might end up having to finish in the next section. Enrolling phase 1 will ensure that you have a nice time and will allow you to plan in case you need some extra time after your lab.

history.content: I am a declared L&S CS junior (senior next year) trying to take EE16B next fall. I remember for this semester when I tried It wasn't possible to enroll until adjustment period because of saved seats for EECS and CS undeclared. Will this be the case again for Fall 18? In which case should I be looking to phase 1 the class and be top of the waitlist or just sign up for waitlist in phase 2 / adjustment period for some 8am lab & disc section (assuming there will for sure be space in one of those)?
